- Yeah.

967
01:05:11,407 --> 01:05:13,341
I guess I could.

968
01:05:13,542 --> 01:05:17,478
Wasn't that the idea with the flours
and everything?

969
01:05:18,981 --> 01:05:23,145
Honestly, I only figured it out
up to "I want you."

970
01:05:24,153 --> 01:05:26,144
Listen, Mr. Crick...

971
01:05:27,123 --> 01:05:28,613
...I think I like you.

972
01:05:29,558 --> 01:05:34,894
And before I do anything rash,
I'd like to make sure.

973
01:05:36,399 --> 01:05:38,458
I'd like you to come up.

974
01:05:40,002 --> 01:05:41,833
I'd be honored.

975
01:05:43,005 --> 01:05:44,404
Great.

976
01:05:47,743 --> 01:05:49,176
<i>Yeah, he was nuts though.</i>

977
01:05:49,378 --> 01:05:53,075
<i>He got caught when he tried</i>
<i>to get the contract notarized.</i>

978
01:05:53,282 --> 01:05:56,046
No. No.

979
01:06:00,623 --> 01:06:01,920
Was it good?

980
01:06:02,525 --> 01:06:03,492
Thank you.

981
01:06:03,693 --> 01:06:06,161
- You're welcome.
- Can I help you?

982
01:06:06,362 --> 01:06:09,559
No, no, I'm gonna put them in the sink.
Go sit down on the couch.

983
01:06:19,308 --> 01:06:20,605
So do you play the guitar?

984
01:06:21,077 --> 01:06:23,568
- What?
- Do you play the guitar?

985
01:06:24,246 --> 01:06:28,512
Terribly. Someone traded me that
for a wedding cake.

986
01:06:28,718 --> 01:06:32,347
Does that mean I have to claim it
on my taxes now?

987
01:06:32,555 --> 01:06:37,015
- No. I'll leave it out of my final report.
- Oh, thanks.

988
01:06:37,994 --> 01:06:39,325
Do you play?

989
01:06:39,528 --> 01:06:41,018
Not really. I only know one song.

990
01:06:41,230 --> 01:06:42,629
Oh, play it.

991
01:06:42,832 --> 01:06:45,062
No, I don't know it that well, actually.

992
01:06:45,267 --> 01:06:48,134
No, come on. I promise I'm not gonna
laugh at you. Play it.

993
01:06:48,337 --> 01:06:50,532
No, no, no. Maybe some other time.

994
01:06:50,740 --> 01:06:52,264
All right.

995
01:09:17,853 --> 01:09:19,115
Ms. Pascal?

996
01:09:19,622 --> 01:09:22,819
- I...
- I know.

997
01:09:23,025 --> 01:09:24,993
I want you too.

998
01:09:44,914 --> 01:09:50,546
<i>Harold's life was filled with moments</i>
<i>both significant and mundane.</i>

999
01:09:50,753 --> 01:09:56,020
<i>But to Harold, those moments</i>
<i>remained entirely indistinguishable...</i>

1000
01:09:56,225 --> 01:09:57,920
<i>... except for this.</i>

1001
01:09:58,594 --> 01:10:03,463
<i>As Ana let out a soft sigh and</i>
<i>repositioned herself against him...</i>

1002
01:10:03,666 --> 01:10:05,793
<i>... Harold knew</i>
<i>somewhere in his heart...</i>

1003
01:10:06,001 --> 01:10:08,799
<i>... that this was one</i>
<i>of the significant moments.</i>

1004
01:10:09,004 --> 01:10:12,872
<i>He knew she was</i>
<i>falling in love with him.</i>

1005
01:10:15,377 --> 01:10:17,242
Professor Hilbert. It's a comedy.

1006
01:10:17,446 --> 01:10:19,175
- What?
- A comedy.

1007
01:10:19,848 --> 01:10:23,841
The woman. The one who hates me.
Ana Pascal?

1008
01:10:24,053 --> 01:10:26,146
- Last night...
- Yeah?

1009
01:10:26,355 --> 01:10:27,982
She's falling in love with me.

1010
01:10:28,190 --> 01:10:29,953
- She is?
- It's like a miracle.

1011
01:10:30,159 --> 01:10:32,491
The voice confirmed it
in the middle of the night.

1012
01:10:32,695 --> 01:10:34,094
Well, that's wonderful, Harold.

1013
01:10:34,296 --> 01:10:37,322
